{
  "texts": [
    "29 adopted a data-driven approach to build ML models based on Li||Cu batteries for electrolyte design and proposed that careful control of electrolyte oxygen content will be essential for Li metal batteries with high coulombic efficiency and enough stability (Fig. 2f).",
    "Whitacre et al.",
    "61 reported a high-throughput screening platform for the discovery of organic electrolytes with high conductivity among a wide range of salt types and concentrations.",
    "Recently, Gao et al.",
    "62 proposed a data-driven approach to probe the origin of the reductive stability of solvents and accelerate the molecular design for advanced electrolytes by combining a graph theory-based algorithm with first-principles calculation of the lowest unoccupied molecular orbital."
  ]
